---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
AMQP (Advance Message Queuing Protocol)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- open standard application layer for MOM
- this protocol can be used with any technology or programming language

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
AMQP Definitions
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Exchanges
- clients always publish a message to an AMQP exchange
- takes a message and routes it to zero or more queues
- based on exchange type and binding (queue name)

# Queues
- bind to exchange using the binding key

# Binding
- bind a queue to an exchange

# Messages
- are sent to message broker/exchange with a routing key.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Exchange Types (image)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Default Exchange: bound automatically to every queue created
- Direct Exchange: one-to-one binding, bound to a queue by a routing key
- Topic Exchange: similar to the direct exchange, with wildcard in routing key
- Headers Exchange: similar to the topic exchange, but binding is based on the
                    message headers
- Fanout Exchange: broadcast, copy the message to all the bound queues
